Executive Profile
Jon Kevin Griffin  Independent Director, Main Street Capital CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships45$229,990
Background

		Mr. Jon Kevin Griffin serves as a Senior Vice President of Financial Planning and Analysis at Novant Health. Mr. Griffin’s responsibilities at the firm primarily includes debt capital market and mergers and acquisition transactions, along with various other strategic analysis projects. From 2007 to October 2012, he served as a Managing Director at Fennebresque & Co., LLC. Mr. Griffin also founded the firm in 2007. Prior to that, he served as a Principal at McColl Partners ... LLC. Mr. Griffin also served as its Partner from 2003 to 2007, where he originated and executed middle market mergers and acquisitions transactions. Prior to that, Mr. Griffin worked in the mergers and acquisitions and corporate finance divisions at Lazard, JP Morgan and Bank of America. He has been an Independent Director of Main Street Capital Corporation since August 3, 2011. Mr. Griffin bulge-bracket investment banking experience consists primarily of executing and originating mergers and acquisitions and fixed income transactions. He has more than 11 years of investment banking experience including five focused exclusively on the middle market. Mr. Griffin has extensive finance and valuation experience, as well as his extensive background in working with middle market companies in an mergers and acquisitions and advisory capacity. He received a Master of Business Administration degree (with honors) from the University of Chicago Graduate School of Business in 1999 and Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration from The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill in 1994.Read Full Background




